Vice President Biden will be embarking on a "Road to Recovery" tour, where he will visit various communities across the country to highlight the impact of the Recovery Act in creating jobs and improving infrastructure. The tour will start with stops in Carlisle, Pennsylvania and Overland Park, Kansas, where Biden will attend groundbreaking events for transportation construction projects. He will then travel to Kalamazoo, Michigan for another groundbreaking ceremony for a road reconstruction project. During this event, Biden will also address the communities affected by the auto industry. The events are open to the press, and media details and logistics are provided in the article.